[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+     91[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mThe problem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m The entity comparison approach has a fundamental limitation that the recipe acknowledges but underplays. Comprehend Medical extracts entities as text spans. The original says "myocardial infarction" and the simplified version says "heart attack." These are the same concept but different text. The pseudocode's [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mfind_matching_entity[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;192;197;206m function is hand-waved without explaining how it handles synonyms. The Python companion uses substring matching, which will miss this case entirely.[K
