[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    232[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The "transformation task, not a generation task" distinction is an important safety framing that most LLM recipes skip. It correctly identifies why simplification is safer than open-ended generation and sets appropriate expectations.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    233[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The failure modes section is genuinely useful. "Meaning drift," "over-simplification," "under-simplification," and "confidence without accuracy" are the real failure modes, described with concrete examples. This section alone justifies the recipe's existence for a reader evaluating whether to build this.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    234[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The readability scoring explanation (Flesch-Kincaid, Flesch Reading Ease, SMOG) with the honest caveat that they measure surface complexity, not conceptual complexity, is exactly the right level of nuance.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    235[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m The sample output (cardiac discharge summary, original vs. simplified) is convincing and demonstrates real value. The simplified version is genuinely better for a patient.[K
[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    236[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m "The Honest Take" delivers a non-obvious insight: "patients don't just want simpler words. They want structure." This is the kind of production experience that makes the cookbook valuable.[K
